role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104idk1665702794063.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/idk1665702794063.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/idk1665702794063.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"idk1665702794063\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Component Editor\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"idk1665702794063__component_editor_22047\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Component Editor to construct application components, such as dynamic and static server pages, and services.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"idk1665702794063__p_d5432e1_d5433e1_d5434e1\">When you create or open a dynamic server page, a static server page, or a service, it is opened in its own Component Editor, as a tab in the central editing area.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"idk1665702794063__topic_d2997e1_d2998e1_d2999e1_d3000e1_d3001e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d931041e60\">\n                       \n Worksheets\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"idk1665702794063__li_d2534e1_d2535e1_d2536e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Define Structure</span>—define the data that the component uses. Insert Entities and Fields from the Toolbox, and arrange them in a structure that reflects a specific view of the data (up or down). The view can affect the component's behavior in retrieving, storing, and deleting data using the component. For example, a component for a shopping cart or order form may use Modeled Entities for CART and ITEM data, and a non-database entity that defines buttons such as Delete and Go to Checkout.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"idk1665702794063__li_d2537e1_d2538e1_d2539e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Design Layout</span>—for dynamic and static server pages, create the layout using HTML and CSS.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"idk1665702794063__li_d2540e1_d2541e1_d2542e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Write Script</span>—define the component behavior using ProcScript and JavaScript (in some circumstances).\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"idk1665702794063__p_d5438e1_d5439e1_d5440e1\">Each worksheet contains its own Resource Browser and editing tools, appropriate to the activity.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"idk1665702794063__topic_d3002e1_d3003e1_d3004e1_d3005e1_d3006e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d931041e90\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"idk1665702794063__li_d2543e1_d2544e1_d2545e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwr1665702624245.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwr1665702624245.html\" title=\"Most components can be created following the same basic procedure.\">Construct a Component</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"idk1665702794063__li_d2546e1_d2547e1_d2548e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"idk1665702794063__li_d2549e1_d2550e1_d2551e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"idk1665702794063__fig_w3429ab1b7b7b7b1_w3430ab1b7b7b7_w3431ab1b7b7_w3432ab1b7_w3433ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Component Editor for Dynamic Server Page: Write Script Worksheet</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Component Editor showing Write Script worksheet\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/cpteditor_ws.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Component Editor for Dynamic Server Page: Write Script Worksheet\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/cpteditor_ws.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/djm1704694970422.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Data Structure</a><p>Every component has a data structure that defines its component entities and fields, and the path required to access the data. The data structure affects the validation rules for data I/O, such as enforcing referential integrity constraints.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528493\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528493\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Component Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Component Editor Use the Component Editor to construct application components, such as dynamic and static server pages, and services. When you create or open a dynamic server page, a static server page, or a service, it is opened in its own Component Editor, as a tab in the central editing area. Worksheets Define Structure —define the data that the component uses. Insert Entities and Fields from the Toolbox, and arrange them in a structure that reflects a specific view of the data (up or down). The view can affect the component's behavior in retrieving, storing, and deleting data using the component. For example, a component for a shopping cart or order form may use Modeled Entities for CART and ITEM data, and a non-database entity that defines buttons such as Delete and Go to Checkout. Design Layout —for dynamic and static server pages, create the layout using HTML and CSS. Write Script —define the component behavior using ProcScript and JavaScript (in some circumstances). Each worksheet contains its own Resource Browser and editing tools, appropriate to the activity. How to Construct a Component Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Figure 1. Component Editor for Dynamic Server Page: Write Script Worksheet Related Links Component Data Structure Every component has a data structure that defines its component entities and fields, and the path required to access the data. The data structure affects the validation rules for data I/O, such as enforcing referential integrity constraints. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}